        public long getTimestampOnLeader()
        Description copied from interface: IHAGatherReleaseTimeRequest
        A timestamp on the leader at the start of the protocol used to agree on the new release time (this can be the commitTime that will be assigned by the leader to the new commit point). This is used to detect problems where the clocks are not synchronized on the services.
        Specified by:
